{{wikipedia}}
==English==
{{see|the wheel}}

===Pronunciation===
*{{AHD|/wēl}}, {{IPA|/wiːl/}}, {{SAMPA|/wi:l/}}
*:Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːl|-iːl]]

===Etymology===
Old English ''hwēoġol'', ''[[hwēol]]'' < Proto-Germanic ''*khwekhwlan'', ''*khwegwlan'' < [[Proto-Indo-European]] '''*kwe-k(w)lo-''' (wheel, circle), a reduplicated form of PIE base '''*k(w)el-''' (to go round). Cognate with Dutch [[wiel]] (''wheel''); Old Church Slavonic [[коло]]; Latin [[colere]] (''to cultivate, inhabit'' = ''turn around''); and Old Norse [[hvél]], '''hjól''' (''wheel'').

====Homophones====
*[[we'll]]
*[[weal]]
*[[wheal]]

===Noun===
{{en-noun-reg}}

# A circular device capable of rotating on its [[axis]], facilitating movement or transportation or performing labour in machines.
# {{slang}} A person with a great deal of [[power]] or [[influence]].
# {{nautical}} The [[instrument]] attached to the [[rudder]] by which a [[vessel]] is [[steered]]. (FM 55-501).

